{"lemma":"ثَوْبٌ","slug":"ثَوْبٌ","root":"ث.#.ب","root_slug":"ث-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ثَوْبٌ","root":"ثوب","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4802"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dress, garment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cloth, material"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"outward appearance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clothes, clothing","tags":["in-plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/θawb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4802","headword_ar":"ثَوْبٌ","root":"vwb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, Msb, K,) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is worn by men, composed of linen, cotton, wool, fur,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaz~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) but [properly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not what is cut out of several pieces, such as the shirt, and trousers, or drawers, &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) [though often applied to a shirt or shift ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamiyS","text_ar":"قَمِيص"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroE","text_ar":"دِرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":") and to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~ap","text_ar":"جُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:] it seems to be so called because the wearer returns to it, or it to the wearer, time after time: (Mgh:) [also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment worn by women and girls over the shift;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSodapN","text_ar":"اُصْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) app., as in the present day,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long gown, reaching to the feet, with very wide sleeves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAbN","text_ar":"ثِيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the pl. of mult.] (T, S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avowaAbN","text_ar":"اَثْوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] (S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avowubN","text_ar":"اَثْوُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avow^ubN","text_ar":"اَثْوُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) the last two being pls. of pauc., and the latter of them being thus pronounced with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"by some of the Arabs because the dammeh immediately after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is deemed difficult of utterance; for which reason they substitute"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in all instances like this. (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Curtains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"are not [properly] called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAb","text_ar":"ثِيَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amotiEapu Albayoti","text_ar":"اَمْتِعَةُ البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) though Es-Sarakhsee uses the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAbu Albayoti","text_ar":"ثِيَابُ البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEal~aqa biviyaAbi","text_ar":"تَعَلَّقَ بِثِيَابِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clung to the curtains"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the House"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"], i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the curtains of the Kaabeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a tropical expression. (A.) ―         -b3-  Sometimes,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used metonymically to signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that veils, covers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protects:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kavawobi A@boni biyDK waqaAhumo bihi\n                      \n                     \n                        fasad~a EalaY Als~aAlikiyna Als~abiylaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like the means of protection adopted by Ibn-Beed: he protected them by it, and closed the way against the passengers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) Ibn-Beed was a wealthy merchant of the tribe of 'Ád, who hamstrung his she-camel upon a mountain-road, and stopped the way [to his abode] with it. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byD","text_ar":"بيض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  In the same manner, also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAbN","text_ar":"ثِيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used to signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weapons."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 63.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avowaAbN","text_ar":"اَثْوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes employed to signify (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wearers of garments;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the wearers'"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodies."},{"kind":"text","text":"(R, TA.) Esh-Shemmákh says, (T,) or Leylà, describing camels, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wamawohaA biA^avowaAbK xifaAfK falaA taraY\n                      \n                     \n                        lahaA  $abahFA A_il~aA Aln~aEaAma Almunaf~araA"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They mounted them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, the travellingcamels, (T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"their ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and thou seest not anything like them, except ostriches scared away."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (T, TA.) And in like manner, also, the dual is employed to signify (assumed tropical:)  The wearer's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what the garments infold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAb","text_ar":"ثِيَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is employed in the same manner. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lil~hi vawobaAhu","text_ar":"لِلّهِ ثَوْبَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To God be he"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his excellence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attributed!"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for nothing but what is excellent is to be attributed to God:] (A:) or it means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lil~hi dar~uhu","text_ar":"لِلّهِ دَرُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To God be attributed the good that hath proceeded from him!"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his good deed!"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alh","text_ar":"اله"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dr","text_ar":"در"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY vawobaYo A^abiY A^ano A^afiyahu","text_ar":"فِى ثَوْبَىْ اَبِى اَنْ اَفِيَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"On me and on my father it rests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be it, that I pay it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY*im~atiY wa*im~apiA^abiY","text_ar":"فِىذِمَّتِى وَذِمَّةِاَبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on my responsibility and the responsibility of my father"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ausolulo viyaAbaka mino viyaAbiY","text_ar":"اُسْلُلْ ثِيَابَكَ مِنْ ثِيَابِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Withdraw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separate, thyself from me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b6-  [The following exs. are mostly, or all, tropical.] ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~i Almay~ita","text_ar":"اـِنِّ المَيِّتَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layuboEavu fiY viyaAbihi Al~atiY yamuwtu fiyhaA","text_ar":"لَيُبْعَثُ فِى ثِيَابِهِ الَّتِى يَمُوتُ فِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) a saying of Mohammad, repeated by Aboo-Sa'eed El-Khudree, when, being about to die, he had called for new garments, and put them on: (TA:) it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the dead will be raised in his garments in which he dies;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to some; and was used in this sense by Aboo-Sa'eed: (ElKhattábee, MF, TA:) or (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agreeably with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his works"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which his life is closed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the state in which he dies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"according as it is good or evil. (TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waviyaAbaka faTah~iro","text_ar":"وَثِيَابَكَ فَطَهِّرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxxiv. 4], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And purify thy garments:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Abbás, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shorten thy garments;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the shortening them is a means of purity: (T:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put not on thy garments in a state of disobedience or unrighteousness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I'Ab, T:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be not perfidious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for [figuratively speaking,] he who is so pollutes his garments: (Fr, T:) or, as some say, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purify thy heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Abbás, T, K:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purify thyself"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKt, T, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from sins,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offences:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKt, TA:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rectify thine actions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy conduct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAno naqiY~u Alv~awobi","text_ar":"فُلَانْ نَقِىُّ الثَّوْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is free from vice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fault:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAhiru Alv~awobi","text_ar":"طَاهِرُ الثَّوْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure in heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nSH","text_ar":"نصح"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danisu Alv~iyaAbi","text_ar":"دَنِسُ الثِّيَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vicious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faulty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfidious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil, in reputation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"actions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the way that he follows"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to religion and morality"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAbisi vawobaYo zuwrK","text_ar":"كَلَابِسِ ثَوْبَىْ زُورٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muta$ab~iEN","text_ar":"مُتَشَبِّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraDa vawobu","text_ar":"اَعْرَضَ ثَوْبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almalobasi","text_ar":"المَلْبَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almilobasi","text_ar":"المِلْبَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruDa","text_ar":"عَرُضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"ثَوْبُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The membrane called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alaY","text_ar":"السَّلَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algirosu","text_ar":"الغِرْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K. See these two words.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Mgh","Msb","K","T","S","A","TA","Fr","IKt"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}